**Stay Safe Online – Prevention Checklist**
- Verify links before clicking – Always check the sender’s email address and hover over links to confirm authenticity.
- Use strong, unique passwords – Mix uppercase, lowercase, numbers, and symbols; avoid reusing the same password.
- Enable two-factor authentication (2FA) – Add an extra layer of security to your accounts.
- Avoid sharing personal details publicly – Keep your phone number, address, and financial info private.
- Be cautious with attachments – Do not download files from unknown or suspicious emails.
- Update software regularly – Keep your operating system, apps, and antivirus up to date.
- Check UPI/Payment requests carefully – Verify the recipient before transferring money.
- Never share UPI PIN or OTP – Banks and payment apps will never ask for these details.
- Report suspicious activity immediately – Use the National Cyber Crime Portal (cybercrime.gov.in).
 - Call the Cyber Crime Helpline (1930) – For urgent fraud or online payment issues.
